<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="156" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,386,1205]" pageId="5" pageNumber="156">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,963,989]" pageId="5" pageNumber="156">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name is a reference to the Latin word ‘ 
<emphasis box="[839,956,963,989]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="156">hypocrites</emphasis>
’ which relates to ‘actor’ or ‘mime’, an allusion to the fact that this group resembles, ‘pretends to be’, 
<emphasis box="[845,978,999,1025]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="156">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Macquart" authorityYear="1834" box="[845,974,999,1025]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Ocyptamus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="156" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Ocyptamus</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
but is not that genus. The name is to be treated as masculine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="156" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,386,1205]" pageId="5" pageNumber="156">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1070,1096]" pageId="5" pageNumber="156">Comments.</emphasis>
This Nearctic genus, corresponding to the former 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Miranda &amp; Skevington &amp; Marshall" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Wiedemann" baseAuthorityYear="1830" box="[913,1173,1071,1097]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Ocyptamus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="156" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fascipennis">
<emphasis box="[913,1173,1071,1097]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="156">Ocyptamus fascipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group, is characterized by distinctive wing markings (
<figureCitation box="[603,685,1107,1133]" captionStart="FIGURES 12–22. 12–15" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1700,1724]" captionTargetBox="[259,1328,566,1667]" captionTargetId="figure-200@6.[248,1339,561,1677]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 12–22. 12–15. Hypocritanus Miranda gen. nov.. 12: Hypocritanus fascipennis (Wiedemann), female, habitus, dorsal view, by Steve Marshall. 13: Hypocritanus fascipennis (Wiedemann) (debu01088980), male, epandrium, ventral view. 14–15. Hypocritanus fascipennis (Wiedemann) (debu00119165), female, terminalia. 14: dorsal view. 15: lateral view. 16–22. Maiana Miranda gen. nov. 16: Maiana pumila (Austen), female, habitus, dorsal view, by Steve Marshall. 17: Maiana sp. (INPA- DIP000172), male, head, dorsal view. 18: Maiana pumila (Austen) (JSS32861), male, wing. 19: Maiana pumila (Austen) (debu00178088), female, scutellum and tergum 1, dorsal view. 20–22. Maiana pumila (Austen) (JSS32861), male, terminalia. 20: epandrium, lateral view. 21: epandrium, ventral view. 22: hypandrium, lateral view. c: cercus; e: epiproct; h: hypandrium; p: postgonite; ph: phallus; s: surstylus; se: subepandrial sclerite; l: lobe; le: lobular expansion; lem: lateral eye margin; o: ocellar triangle; pem: posterior eye margin; t1: tergum 1." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4401373" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4401373/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="156">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
) and the medial swelling on the 2nd abdominal segment (
<figureCitation box="[1339,1423,1107,1133]" captionStart="FIGURES 12–22. 12–15" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1700,1724]" captionTargetBox="[259,1328,566,1667]" captionTargetId="figure-200@6.[248,1339,561,1677]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 12–22. 12–15. Hypocritanus Miranda gen. nov.. 12: Hypocritanus fascipennis (Wiedemann), female, habitus, dorsal view, by Steve Marshall. 13: Hypocritanus fascipennis (Wiedemann) (debu01088980), male, epandrium, ventral view. 14–15. Hypocritanus fascipennis (Wiedemann) (debu00119165), female, terminalia. 14: dorsal view. 15: lateral view. 16–22. Maiana Miranda gen. nov. 16: Maiana pumila (Austen), female, habitus, dorsal view, by Steve Marshall. 17: Maiana sp. (INPA- DIP000172), male, head, dorsal view. 18: Maiana pumila (Austen) (JSS32861), male, wing. 19: Maiana pumila (Austen) (debu00178088), female, scutellum and tergum 1, dorsal view. 20–22. Maiana pumila (Austen) (JSS32861), male, terminalia. 20: epandrium, lateral view. 21: epandrium, ventral view. 22: hypandrium, lateral view. c: cercus; e: epiproct; h: hypandrium; p: postgonite; ph: phallus; s: surstylus; se: subepandrial sclerite; l: lobe; le: lobular expansion; lem: lateral eye margin; o: ocellar triangle; pem: posterior eye margin; t1: tergum 1." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4401373" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4401373/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="156">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
). Some codons in the cytochrome B gene are so far unique to this genus (
<bibRefCitation author="Miranda, G. F. G. &amp; Skevington, J. H. &amp; Marshall, S. A. &amp; Kelso, S." box="[964,1195,1143,1170]" pageId="5" pageNumber="156" pagination="161 - 176" refId="ref17512" refString="Miranda, G. F. G., Skevington, J. H., Marshall, S. A. &amp; Kelso, S. (2016) The genus Ocyptamus Macquart (Diptera: Syrphidae): A molecular phylogenetic analysis. Arthropod Systematics and Phylogeny, 74, 161 - 176." type="journal article" year="2016">
<taxonomicName authority="Miranda &amp; Skevington &amp; Marshall, 2020" authorityName="Miranda &amp; Skevington &amp; Marshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[964,1061,1143,1169]" class="Gastropoda" family="Goniodorididae" genus="Miranda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nudibranchia" pageId="5" pageNumber="170" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">Miranda</taxonomicName>
<emphasis box="[1069,1119,1143,1169]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="156">et al</emphasis>
. 2016
</bibRefCitation>
). Further information on this group can be found in 
<bibRefCitation author="Mengual, X. &amp; Miranda, G. F. G. &amp; Thompson, F. C." box="[486,734,1179,1205]" pageId="5" pageNumber="156" pagination="1 - 44" refId="ref17217" refString="Mengual, X., Miranda, G. F. G. &amp; Thompson, F. C. (2018) Unraveling Ocyptamus and the Baccha legacy (Diptera: Syrphidae): redefinition of groups and new species descriptions. Zootaxa, 4461 (1), 1 - 44. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4461.1.1" type="journal article" year="2018">
Mengual 
<emphasis box="[593,642,1179,1205]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="156">et al</emphasis>
. (2018)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
